[There have been sporadic cases of Crimean-Congo hemorrhagic fever (CCHF) in various parts of Pakistan this year (2014). The above report provides a summary of the situation so far this year in Pakistan and of the tick reservoir and domestic animals hosts.

A map of the provinces of Pakistan showing the location mentioned above can be accessed at http://www.mapsofworld.com/pakistan/pakistan-political-map.html, and a HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2792201,825. - Mod.TY]
